    "detail": "ONLY shape where online LOSES to existing (ex/on=0.932, ~6.8%). Root cause is a seed warp pick: at chunk=16384 the online kernel prefers num_warps=16 (938us) but the heuristic seeds num_warps=32 (1065us); the online-rescale recurrence is more register-heavy than the T1 rolled reduction so w32 over-subscribes at this row width. Online at its best config (w16, 938us) would BEAT existing (993us). Confined to this one mid-wide shape; not a correctness/structural issue."
